	Stockholders.&#148; We will not be selling any shares of our common stock in this offering and will not receive any of the proceeds from the sale of the shares being sold by the selling stockholders.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We obtained the industry, market and competitive position data used throughout this prospectus from internal company surveys and management
	estimates as well as from industry and general publications and research, surveys and studies conducted by third parties. We believe these internal company surveys and management estimates are reliable; however, no independent sources have verified
	such surveys and estimates.
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Third-party
</FONT>
	industry and general publications, research, studies and surveys generally state that the information contained therein has been obtained from sources believed to be
	reliable, although they do not guarantee the accuracy or completeness of such information. While we believe that each of these studies and publications is reliable, neither we nor the selling stockholders have independently verified any of the data
	from
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	third-party
</FONT>
	sources and cannot guarantee its accuracy and completeness.
</P>

	&#147;we,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; or &#147;us&#148; are to AdvancePierre Foods Holdings,&nbsp;Inc. and its consolidated subsidiaries, (2)&nbsp;references to &#147;AdvancePierre&#148; are to AdvancePierre Foods Holdings,&nbsp;Inc. exclusive of its
	subsidiaries, (3)&nbsp;references to &#147;APF Holdco&#148; are to Pierre Holdco,&nbsp;Inc., a direct
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	wholly-owned
</FONT>
	subsidiary of AdvancePierre, and (4)&nbsp;references to &#147;APF&#148; are to AdvancePierre
	Foods,&nbsp;Inc., an indirect
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	wholly-owned
</FONT>
	subsidiary of AdvancePierre and a direct subsidiary of APF Holdco.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week
</FONT>

	2015&#148; are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week

<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	53-week
</FONT>
	period ended January&nbsp;3, 2015, references
	to &#147;fiscal 2013&#148; are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week
</FONT>
	period ended December&nbsp;28, 2013, references to &#147;fiscal 2012&#148; are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week
</FONT>
	period ended
	December&nbsp;29, 2012 and references to &#147;fiscal 2011&#148; are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week
</FONT>
	period ended December&nbsp;31, 2011. References to &#147;Q4 2016&#148; are to the 13-week period ended December 31, 2016 and
	references to &#147;Q4 2015&#148; are to the 13-week period ended January 2, 2016. References to &#147;Q3 2016&#148; are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	13-week
</FONT>
	period ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and references to &#147;Q3 2015&#148;
	are to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	13-week
</FONT>
	period ended October&nbsp;3, 2015. References to the &#147;2016 YTD period&#148; are to the fiscal year to date period ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and references to &#147;2015 YTD
	period&#148; are to the fiscal year to date period ended October&nbsp;3, 2015. Both the 2016 YTD period and the 2015 YTD period consisted of 39&nbsp;weeks. In this prospectus, (1)&nbsp;financial data for fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013, and
	balance sheet data as of January&nbsp;2, 2016 and January&nbsp;3, 2015, is derived from our audited consolidated financial statements included elsewhere in this prospectus, (2)&nbsp;financial data for fiscal 2012 and fiscal 2011, and balance sheet
	data as of December&nbsp;28, 2013, December&nbsp;29, 2012 and December&nbsp;31, 2011, is derived from our unaudited consolidated financial statements that are not included in this prospectus and (3)&nbsp;financial data for Q3 2016, Q3 2015, the 2016
	YTD period, the 2015 YTD period and balance sheet data as of October&nbsp;1, 2016, is derived from our unaudited consolidated interim financial statements included elsewhere in this prospectus.

<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
<A NAME="D304963DS1A_HTM_ROM304963_4">
</A>
	PROSPECTUS SUMMARY
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<I>
	This summary highlights certain significant aspects of our business and this offering. This is a summary of information contained elsewhere
	in this prospectus, is not complete and does not contain all of the information that you should consider before investing in our common stock. You should carefully read the entire prospectus, including the information presented under the sections
	entitled &#147;Risk Factors&#148; and &#147;Special Note Regarding
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Forward-Looking
</FONT>
	Statements&#148; and our consolidated financial statements and the related notes thereto included elsewhere in this
	prospectus, before making a decision to invest in our common stock. This summary contains
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	forward-looking
</FONT>
	statements that involve risks and uncertainties. Our actual results may differ significantly from
	future results contemplated in the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	forward-looking
</FONT>
	statements as a result of certain factors such as those set forth in the sections entitled &#147;Risk Factors&#148; and &#147;Special Note Regarding
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Forward-Looking
</FONT>
	Statements.&#148; When making an investment decision, you should also read the discussion under &#147;Basis of Presentation&#148; for the definition of certain terms used in this prospectus and other
	matters described in this prospectus.
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Who We Are
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are a leading national producer and distributor of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added,
</FONT>
	convenient,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, sandwich components and other entr&eacute;es and snacks. We hold the number one or number two market share position by sales or volume in nearly all
	our major product categories, with net sales of $1.5&nbsp;billion in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and $1.6&nbsp;billion in fiscal 2015. We offer a differentiated value proposition to our customers due to our scale, broad product
	portfolio, customization capabilities, national distribution and food safety track record.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We market and distribute approximately 2,600
	stock keeping units (&#147;SKUs&#148;) across all day parts in multiple product categories, including:
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(1)&nbsp;ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches,
	peanut butter and jelly (&#147;PB&amp;J&#148;) sandwiches and hamburgers; (2)&nbsp;sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger and chicken patties and Philly steaks; and (3)&nbsp;other entr&eacute;es
	and snacks, such as country fried steak, stuffed entr&eacute;es, chicken tenders and cinnamon dough bites. In the twelve months ended October 1, 2016, 67.5% of our net sales were attributable to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fast-growing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and sandwich components categories. Our products are shipped frozen to our customers and
	sold under our commercial and retail brands, as well as private label and licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We control more steps within the production
	process than most of our competitors. This integrated approach allows us to add value throughout our processes, generate attractive margins and provides us with a significant competitive advantage. Our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	processes include recipe formulation,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	pre-preparation
</FONT>
	by chopping, breading, seasoning and marinating, food preparation by baking, charring, frying and
	grilling, assembly and packaging. Our integrated bread and biscuit production capabilities are a key differentiator due to proprietary formulations that we believe produce superior tasting sandwiches.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We sell to a diverse set of over 3,000 customers and have an average relationship tenure of approximately 20&nbsp;years with our top 20
	customers. We employ a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach, which is rooted in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	market-leading
</FONT>
	research and development (&#147;R&amp;D&#148;) capabilities, product quality and
	customer service. We have dedicated marketing and sales teams for each of our channels to serve the specific needs of our customers. We enjoy &#147;category captain&#148; status in many of our product categories with our largest foodservice
	customers. In many cases, we collaborate with our customers to develop new products, customizing recipes and flavors in a cost efficient manner. We believe our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach is a competitive
	advantage that helps our customers grow their businesses and, in turn, accelerates our organic growth and profitability.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We sell our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	products to the foodservice, retail and convenience channels, which correspond to our three core segments. We also sell our products in the industrial channel. We believe our diversification across
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	1
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	these channels provides us with a stable revenue base through economic cycles. In the twelve months ended October 1, 2016, 54.7% of our net sales were generated from our Foodservice segment,
	where our commercial brands are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers. In our Retail segment, in addition to selling our branded products, we also leverage our R&amp;D
	capabilities to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	exclusive products and packaging designs with our customers under their private label brands. In our Convenience segment, we are a leading supplier of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and sandwich components to national and regional convenience chains and vending providers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have an attractive financial profile with steady, organic volume growth, healthy margins, modest capital expenditures and limited working
	capital requirements. These characteristics enable our business to generate strong cash flows. Our earnings profile also benefits from a lean selling, general and administrative (&#147;SG&amp;A&#148;) cost structure and a scaled, efficient supply
	chain network. We intend to use these attributes to enhance stockholder value by paying regular dividends, reducing our indebtedness, strategically deploying our capital to fund organic growth opportunities and financing value-enhancing
	acquisitions.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016, we generated $1.5&nbsp;billion in net sales, $114.8&nbsp;million in net
	income, $97.8&nbsp;million in Adjusted Net Income and $287.9&nbsp;million in Adjusted EBITDA. In fiscal 2015, we generated $1.6&nbsp;billion in net sales, $37.1&nbsp;million in net income, $66.8&nbsp;million in Adjusted Net Income and
	$260.2&nbsp;million in Adjusted EBITDA. Our net sales, Adjusted Net Income and Adjusted EBITDA in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 reflect a compound annual growth rate (&#147;CAGR&#148;) of 1.2%, 337.1% and 20.8%, respectively, since
	fiscal 2013. In the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and fiscal 2015, we also generated $186.6&nbsp;million and $157.2&nbsp;million, respectively, of cash flow from operating activities. See &#147;&#151;Summary Historical Consolidated
	Financial Data&#148; for reconciliations of Adjusted Net Income and Adjusted EBITDA to net income.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Our Recent Performance and the APF
	Way
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	During 2013 and 2014, our board of directors transformed our senior management by hiring John Simons and four of the ten other
	members of our current executive team. This new team revamped our cost structure, budgeting tools and pricing methodology by implementing a continuous improvement program that we call the &#147;APF Way.&#148; The APF Way uses a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	data-driven
</FONT>
	analytical framework to drive growth and profitability through improved commercial
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	decision-making,
</FONT>
	excellence in sales and marketing and productivity in
	procurement, logistics and production.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;

<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe the APF Way has fundamentally changed the cost structure of our business and has
	been a major factor in our recent volume, sales and profitability growth. Initially, we focused on reducing our cost structure by executing on productivity initiatives and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	re-aligning
</FONT>
	trade promotion
	allowances, resulting in approximately $155.0&nbsp;million in implemented annualized savings from 2013 to October&nbsp;1, 2016. In addition, we eliminated approximately $155.0&nbsp;million of sales associated with lower margin contracts. We have
	invested in new systems and processes that enable us to deliver continuous productivity savings and effectively manage margins and profitability. Our Adjusted EBITDA margin, which we calculate as Adjusted EBITDA divided by net sales, expanded from
	10.9% in fiscal 2013 to 18.6% in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016, even as our raw material costs increased. Our net sales and volume grew at a CAGR of 2.7% and 5.2%, respectively, in our three core segments from fiscal 2013 to the
	twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016. Going forward, we expect these investments and discipline will allow us to continue to deliver overall growth and attractive margins.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G00E28.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Our Segments
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We manage and report our operations in four segments with Foodservice, Retail and Convenience representing our core segments. Our fourth
	segment, Industrial, consists of sales to other food producers under
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	short-term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-manufacturing
</FONT>
	agreements.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G20Q53.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	3
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage10"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Foodservice.
</I>
</B>
	The foodservice industry supplies the diverse U.S.
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	&#147;food-away-from-home&#148;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</FONT>
	industry. The foodservice industry had $232&nbsp;billion of sales in 2015 and is expected to have 2.3%
	annual growth over the next five years, according to Technomic&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;Technomic&#148;) data prepared in 2016. Our Foodservice customers include leading national and regional distributors, who then sell our products to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-customers
</FONT>
	such as restaurant operators, schools, healthcare providers, hospitality providers, the U.S. military and grocery deli counters. We supply 95 of the largest 100 school districts in the United States,
	directly and through distributors, and work closely with school districts to develop nutritious meal options with good quality and value. We also directly supply many national restaurant chains. We sell a diverse portfolio of products into the
	foodservice channel, including
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, PB&amp;J sandwiches and hamburgers, sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger and chicken patties and Philly steaks, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as country fried steak, stuffed entr&eacute;es, chicken tenders and cinnamon dough bites. We primarily sell our
	products under our own commercial brands, which are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers. Commercial and private label brands accounted for 71.5% and 28.5%, respectively, of our
	Foodservice net sales for fiscal 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Retail.
</I>
</B>
	Frozen and refrigerated handhelds, which includes
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, accounted for $4.1&nbsp;billion of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	industry-wide
</FONT>
	retail sales in 2015, with 5.3% annual growth since 2010,
	according to Information Resources,&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;IRI&#148;) data prepared in 2016. Within frozen and refrigerated handhelds, breakfast handhelds accounted for $1.2&nbsp;billion of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	industry-wide
</FONT>
	retail
	sales in 2015, with 14.6% annual growth since 2010, according to IRI data prepared in 2016. We serve a wide array of retail customers including national and regional grocery chains, major warehouse club stores, mass retailers and dollar stores. Key
	products that we sell into the retail channel include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, grilled chicken sandwiches and stuffed pockets, sandwich
	components, such as chicken patties and Philly steaks, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as stuffed chicken breasts. In addition to selling our branded products, we also leverage our R&amp;D capabilities to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	exclusive products and packaging designs with our Retail customers under their private label brands. For fiscal 2015, 69.4% of our Retail net sales were attributable to our retail brands, such as
<I>
	Barber
</I>
	,
<I>
	Pierre
</I>
	and
<I>
	Fast Fixin&#146;
</I>
	, 29.8% to private label brands and the rest to licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Convenience.
</I>
</B>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Industry-wide
</FONT>
	prepared food sales in the convenience channel were
	$46.8&nbsp;billion in 2015, with approximately 9.3% annual growth since 2012, according to National Association of Convenience Stores (&#147;NACS&#148;) data prepared in 2016. Our Convenience customers include national and regional convenience
	chains and vending providers. We partner with our Convenience customers to develop customized,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches and hamburgers,
	sandwich components, such as chicken patties, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as cinnamon dough bites. For fiscal 2015, 77.6% of our Convenience net sales were attributable to our retail brands, such as
<I>
	Big AZ
</I>
	, 21.6% to private
	label brands and the rest to licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Industrial.
</I>
</B>
	In order to optimize capacity utilization across our production
	network, we opportunistically enter into
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	short-term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-manufacturing
</FONT>
	agreements with other food producers, such as packaged food companies. Due to the lower margin
	nature of this business, we have strategically reduced our percentage of net sales generated by this segment from 15.7% in fiscal 2013 to 5.1% in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Our Strengths
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe
	the following strengths differentiate us from our competitors and will contribute to our ongoing success:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Leading Market Positions in Attractive,
	Growing Categories
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We hold the number one or number two market share position by volume in nearly all of our major product categories
	and are well positioned to capitalize on growth in our markets. We are the number one player with
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	4
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage11"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	market shares ranging from approximately 30% to 65% in our top five product categories, which represent 68% of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Within most of our major product categories, we are
	the only
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	full-service
</FONT>
	operator of scale and compete against smaller, regional players with limited product breadth, production capacity and capabilities. We typically do not compete against large packaged food
	companies given our foodservice focus and the customization requirements of our customers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We produce over 600&nbsp;million sandwiches
	per year and 67.5% of our net sales in the twelve months ended October 1, 2016 were related to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and sandwich components. We are a leading provider
	of lunch and dinner sandwiches to the foodservice, retail and convenience channels. Our superior bread quality is an important purchase driver for our sandwiches.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G39I04.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Long-Standing,
</FONT>
	Collaborative Customer Relationships Create a High Barrier to
	Entry
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our strong customer relationships across a diverse set of customers provide a significant competitive advantage and create a
	high barrier to entry. For fiscal 2015, our top ten customers accounted for 53.4% of our net sales, with our two largest customers, Sysco Corporation and U.S. Foods,&nbsp;Inc., accounting for 13.6% and 12.0%, respectively, of our net sales in fiscal
	2015. Our two largest customers collectively source over 1,700 SKUs from our portfolio and buy across multiple contracts for a diverse set of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-customers,
</FONT>
	making us an important supplier and giving us a
	stable and consistent revenue base.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have deep and collaborative relationships with an average tenure of approximately 20&nbsp;years
	with our top 20 customers. We maintain our relationships through our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	segment-focused
</FONT>
	marketing teams and an experienced sales force of approximately 100 associates who work closely with customers to meet their
	needs. Our foodservice commercial brands are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers for their consistent food safety, premium quality and taste profile. Given our track record, we
	enjoy &#147;category captain&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	5
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage12"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	status in many of our product categories. We produce approximately 2,600 SKUs for our customers, who source a high volume and a variety of products from us, making us an important supplier and
	partner. We expect to continue to have a competitive advantage as our customers focus on large scale suppliers in order to streamline and optimize their supply chains.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We offer a differentiated value proposition to our customers due to our scale, broad product portfolio, customization capabilities, national
	distribution and food safety track record.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Leader in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	On-Trend,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Fast-to-Market
</FONT>
</FONT>
	New Product Development
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach, which is rooted in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	market-leading
</FONT>
	R&amp;D capabilities, product quality and customer service, differentiates us from our competitors and has
	allowed us to accelerate our organic growth and improve our profitability. Our product innovation and R&amp;D expertise span areas such as flavor development, recipe formulation, nutrition science, bakery science and food safety. In recent years, we
	have enhanced our new product development and customer insight capabilities, and, in 2015, we opened a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	state-of-the-art
</FONT>
</FONT>
</FONT>
	3,200
	square foot R&amp;D facility in West Chester, Ohio.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The food industry today is characterized by rapidly changing menus and evolving
	consumer taste profiles. In this environment, our customers value our ability to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	new products with flavor profiles that differentiate their offerings and successfully commercialize new products with
	speed and efficiency. We launched 600 new SKUs in the last three years, accounting for 12.7% of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Our innovation, sales force and marketing teams collaborate with customers to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	highly customized products and are able to mobilize quickly to respond to customer requests.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Scale
	and Production Efficiency with a National Distribution Footprint
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We benefit from a national, scaled production, procurement and
	logistics network with low production, freight and warehousing costs. We believe our efficient cost structure provides a sustainable competitive advantage and enables us to offer a customized and varied set of products to our customers at
	competitive prices.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have two integrated bakery facilities which allow us to source approximately 65% of our bread
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-house
</FONT>
	(excluding bread for our PB&amp;J sandwiches). Our eleven production facilities benefit from economies of scale, which when combined with our national distribution capabilities, differentiate us from our
	competitors and make us a valuable supplier for both national and regional customers. Except for the production facility previously owned by Allied Specialty Foods,&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;Allied&#148;), which we acquired in October 2016 and are in the
	process of improving, all of our facilities have achieved Safe Quality Food (&#147;SQF&#148;) Level&nbsp;3 food safety certification, the highest level of such certification from the Global Food Safety Initiative (&#147;GFSI&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Attractive Financial Profile
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have an
	attractive financial profile with steady, organic volume growth in our core segments, healthy Adjusted EBITDA margins, modest capital expenditures and limited working capital requirements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are able to deliver attractive Adjusted EBITDA margins due to the high
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	nature of our
	products. Our margin profile is well protected given our ability to proactively adjust pricing frequently to reflect input cost movements with minimal lag time. Only 16.2% of our net sales in fiscal 2015 were subject to fixed price arrangements. We
	also have a lean and scalable cost structure. We plan to continue leveraging the APF Way to deliver operational productivity savings, improve our business mix and increase the effectiveness of our trade promotion allowances. Our business has
	relatively low capital expenditure requirements, with maintenance expenditures typically averaging approximately 1% of our net sales.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	6
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage13"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Proven Acquisition Expertise
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have a successful track record of sourcing, executing and integrating acquisitions, beginning with the combination of Pierre
	Foods,&nbsp;Inc., APF&#146;s predecessor, with Advance Food Company,&nbsp;Inc. and Advance Brands,&nbsp;LLC in 2010. Given our scale and breadth of capabilities, we believe we are well positioned to consolidate the fragmented industry in which we
	operate. We maintain a highly disciplined approach to acquisitions, focusing on opportunities that diversify our products, add production capabilities, expand production capacity and allow for meaningful synergy realization. In addition to realizing
	cost synergies, we leverage our sales teams to expand distribution of newly acquired brands and products and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	cross-sell
</FONT>
	across our channels to drive sales synergies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Since 2011, we have completed four accretive acquisitions. In June 2011, we acquired Barber Foods,&nbsp;LLC (&#147;Barber Foods&#148;), a
	producer of premium stuffed entr&eacute;es, which strengthened our retail presence and expanded our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	chicken-based
</FONT>
	product offering. In January 2015, we acquired the wholesale business and production assets of
	Landshire,&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;Landshire&#148;), which broadened our portfolio of premium sandwiches to include sliced meat sandwiches and added incremental,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	margin-enhancing
</FONT>
	baking and assembly production
	capabilities. In April 2015, we acquired the business and production assets of Better Bakery,&nbsp;LLC (&#147;Better Bakery&#148;) to expand into stuffed sandwiches, one of the largest
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwich categories. Our acquisitions of Barber Foods, Landshire and Better Bakery contributed $166.4&nbsp;million of incremental net sales in fiscal 2015.
	In October 2016, we acquired Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products, which we expect will expand our market position in Philly steaks by adding fully cooked product offerings, expand our geographic reach and increase our
	sandwich component production capacity.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Talented Management Team with a Track Record of Driving Growth and Reducing Costs
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Since 2013, we have assembled an experienced management team through strategic hiring of key leaders and expanded organizational capabilities
	in R&amp;D, sales and marketing. Our management team has an average of 25&nbsp;years of expertise in the foodservice, retail and convenience industries and has demonstrated its ability to deliver on key strategic initiatives, which have transformed
	business performance. In the last two years, our management team&#146;s key accomplishments include implementation of the APF Way, successful integration of two
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-enhancing
</FONT>
	acquisitions and significant
	margin improvement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our management team had been led by our President and Chief Executive Officer John Simons since October 2013. On
	November&nbsp;9, 2016, in response to Mr.&nbsp;Simons&#146; planned retirement in 2017, we announced a succession and transition plan for our President and Chief Executive Officer positions. As a part of the plan, Christopher Sliva, who has over a
	decade of experience as a public food company executive, became our President and a member of our board of directors. It is anticipated that Mr.&nbsp;Simons will remain as our Chief Executive Officer until March&nbsp;31, 2017, when he will retire
	and be succeeded by Mr.&nbsp;Sliva as our President and Chief Executive Officer.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Our Strategy
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Expand Our Market Leading Positions in Growing Channels and Categories
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are focused on expanding our leadership position within our core segments of Foodservice, Retail and Convenience.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	breakfast sandwich category is a
	key growth opportunity for us. We hold the number one position with a 64% market share in breakfast sandwiches sold in the convenience channel. We are also the largest supplier of private label breakfast sandwiches in the retail channel, with a 56%
	market share, according to IRI data prepared in 2016. Private label sales of retail frozen breakfast sandwiches are underpenetrated compared
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	7
</P>

<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	to the frozen food market and therefore we believe poised for significant growth. We will continue to leverage our sandwich expertise and customer relationships to grow our share in breakfast
	sandwiches in the retail channel and with foodservice distributors and schools.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe we have multiple growth opportunities across
	our core segments. In Foodservice, we plan to expand distribution of our products to new customers, such as coffee shops, theaters, grocery deli counters and hospitality providers. In Retail, in addition to growing our sandwich business, we are
	launching product extensions for
<I>
	Barber Foods
</I>
	and
<I>
	Better Bakery
</I>
	and expanding distribution within rapidly growing dollar stores. In Convenience, we are expanding our breakfast product portfolio and launching
<I>
	Better Bakery
</I>
	products.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are also expanding our lineup of products to take advantage of recent consumer trends. We have successfully launched
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	snacking-oriented
</FONT>
	products, such as popcorn chicken, PB&amp;J snack bars and cinnamon dough bites, and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	better-for-you
</FONT>
</FONT>
	products, such as
	antibiotic,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	hormone-free
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	burgers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Drive Growth Through
	Focus on Innovation
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our product categories offer potential for
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	product innovation.
	We believe our innovation capabilities, combined with our investments in consumer insights and our ability to partner with customers to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	products, will enable us to continue to introduce successful
	new products to drive sales growth and margin improvement across our portfolio.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our R&amp;D team is focused on developing products in
	line with key consumer trends, such as breakfast sandwiches,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	better-for-you
</FONT>
</FONT>
	products and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	snacking-oriented
</FONT>
	products. Examples of
	products in our innovation pipeline include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	breakfast sandwiches that meet the new
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	K-12
</FONT>
	nutrition guidelines,
	premium offerings for club stores and new limited time offers for key convenience store chain customers. We are also partnering with various customers to develop
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	on-trend,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	protein-based
</FONT>
	snacks.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Deliver Attractive Margins through Dynamic Pricing and Leveraging the APF Way
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe we are well positioned to deliver attractive margins given the high
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	nature of
	our products, our dynamic pricing model and our ability to generate ongoing productivity savings by leveraging the APF Way. In addition, our focus on improving our product mix, leveraging our scalable organization structure and realizing synergies
	from acquisitions supports our margin profile. Under the APF Way, we are implementing multiple initiatives across the areas of production, procurement, commercial and logistics that we expect will deliver ongoing productivity savings and help offset
	potential operational headwinds and cost inflation.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Acquire
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Value-Enhancing
</FONT>
	Businesses
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe our scale and integration expertise allow us to make
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-enhancing
</FONT>
	acquisitions. We
	operate in a highly fragmented industry with many opportunities to execute accretive transactions. For example, in October 2016, we acquired Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products, which we expect will expand our market
	position in Philly steaks by adding fully cooked product offerings, expand our geographic reach and increase our sandwich component production capacity. Our integration expertise allows us to rapidly capture cost synergies and we are able to
	generate revenue synergies by leveraging existing customer relationships and marketing expertise to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	cross-sell
</FONT>
	products across channels. Our management team has an active pipeline of acquisition opportunities
	and maintains a regular dialogue with potential targets.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Return Capital and Reduce Debt
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe our capital structure enables us to invest in our business and reduce our indebtedness, creating value for our stockholders. We also
	expect to return capital to our stockholders through regular dividend payments. We paid a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.14 per share on September 28, 2016 and December 6, 2016.&nbsp;In addition, on December 16, 2016, we announced that our
	board of directors intends to increase the
</P>

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Corporate Information
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	AdvancePierre was incorporated in Delaware on December&nbsp;5, 2008 as Pierre Foods Holding Corporation and changed its name to AdvancePierre
	Foods Holdings,&nbsp;Inc. on March&nbsp;16, 2016. On July&nbsp;20, 2016, we completed our initial public offering of 21,390,000 shares of our common stock, which included the full exercise of the underwriters&#146; option to purchase additional
	shares, at a price of $21.00. Upon completion of our initial public offering, our common stock was listed on the NYSE under the symbol &#147;APFH.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our executive offices are located at 9987 Carver Road, Blue Ash, Ohio 45242, and our telephone number at that location is
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(800)&nbsp;969-2747.
</FONT>
	We maintain a website at www.advancepierre.com. The information contained
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
</DIV>

	on or accessible through our corporate website or any other website that we may maintain is not part of this prospectus or the registration statement of which this prospectus is a part.

<EFX_STOCKHOLDERS>
<A NAME="FIS_STOCKHOLDERS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Our Principal Stockholders
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Prior to the completion of this offering, funds managed by Oaktree (our &#147;principal stockholders&#148;) beneficially owned 57.2% of our
	common stock. Oaktree is a leader among global investment managers specializing in alternative investments, with $99.8&nbsp;billion in assets under management as of September&nbsp;30, 2016. The firm emphasizes an opportunistic,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-oriented
</FONT>
	and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	risk-controlled
</FONT>
	approach to investments in distressed debt, corporate debt (including high yield debt and senior loans), control investing, convertible
	securities, real estate and listed equities. Headquartered in Los Angeles, the firm has over 900 employees and offices in 18 cities worldwide.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	After the completion of this offering, our principal stockholders will beneficially own&nbsp;44.0% of our common stock, or&nbsp;41.9% of our
	common stock if the underwriters exercise in full their option to purchase additional shares from certain of the selling stockholders. As a result, Oaktree will continue to have significant influence over us and decisions made by our stockholders
	and may have interests that differ from yours. See &#147;Risk factors&#151;Risks Related to this Offering and Ownership of Our Common Stock&#151;Oaktree will continue to have significant influence over us after this offering, which could limit your
	ability to influence the outcome of key transactions, including a change of control.&#148; We also entered into a new stockholders agreement and an amended and restated registration rights agreement with our principal stockholders in connection with
	our initial public offering. For more information regarding these agreements, see &#147;Certain Relationships and Related Party Transactions&#151;Stockholders Agreement&#148; and &#147;&#151;Registration Rights Agreement.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Oaktree currently owns a majority of the voting power of all outstanding shares of our common stock. As a result, we currently are a
	&#147;controlled company&#148; within the meaning of the rules of the NYSE. Upon completion of this offering, we will no longer be a &#147;controlled company&#148; within the meaning of the corporate governance standards of the NYSE. See
	&#147;Principal and Selling Stockholders&#148; and &#147;Risk Factors&#151;Risks Related to this Offering and Ownership of Our Common Stock&#151;Upon completion of this offering, we will no longer be a &#147;controlled company&#148; within the
	meaning of the NYSE. However, we will continue to qualify for, and may rely on, exemptions from certain corporate governance requirements that would otherwise provide protection to stockholders of other companies during a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	one-year
</FONT>
	transition period.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Recent Developments
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Allied Acquisition
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	On October&nbsp;7,
	2016, we acquired all of the outstanding voting interests of Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products, for $60.0&nbsp;million in cash, subject to a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	post-closing
</FONT>
	adjustment estimated to be
	approximately $2.5&nbsp;million. We expect this acquisition will expand our market position in Philly steaks by adding fully cooked product offerings, expand our geographic reach and increase our sandwich component production capacity. The
	acquisition is also expected to provide cost synergies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Succession and Transition Plan for Our President and Chief Executive Officer Positions
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	On November&nbsp;9, 2016, we announced that our board of directors approved a succession and transition plan for our President and
	Chief Executive Officer positions. As a part of the plan, Mr.&nbsp;Sliva became our President and a member of our board of directors on November&nbsp;14, 2016. It is anticipated that Mr.&nbsp;Simons will remain as our Chief Executive Officer until
	March&nbsp;31, 2017, when he will retire and be succeeded by Mr.&nbsp;Sliva as our President and Chief Executive Officer. Mr.&nbsp;Simons will remain a member of our board of directors until the date of the 2017 annual meeting of our stockholders.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Notes Offering
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	On December&nbsp;7, 2016, we issued $400 million aggregate principal amount of our 5.50% senior notes due 2024 (the &#147;notes&#148;) in a
	private placement to &#147;qualified institutional buyers&#148; as defined in Rule&nbsp;144A under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#147;Securities Act&#148;), and outside the United States to non-U.S. persons pursuant to Regulation S
	under the Securities Act. The notes mature on December&nbsp;15, 2024 and bear interest at a rate of 5.50% per annum, payable semi-annually on June&nbsp;15 and December&nbsp;15 of each year, commencing on June&nbsp;15, 2017.&nbsp;On December&nbsp;7,
	2016, we used the net proceeds of the offering, together with cash on hand, to repay $400 million of outstanding borrowings under our first lien term loan and to pay estimated fees and expenses of $5 million. In connection with the repayment of $400
	million of outstanding borrowings under our first lien term loan, we estimate that we will expense $6.3&nbsp;million of unamortized loan origination fees and original issue discount.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Repricing of Our First Lien Term Loan
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	On
	December&nbsp;7, 2016, we entered into a repricing amendment to the credit agreement governing our first lien term loan.&nbsp;The amendment reduced the margins applicable to our first lien term loan from 2.75% per annum (subject to a leverage-based
	step-down to 2.50%) to 2.00% per annum in the case of base rate loans, and from 3.75% per annum (subject to a leverage-based step-down to 3.50%) to 3.00% per annum in the case of LIBOR loans (subject to a 1.00% floor on LIBOR loans). The amendment
	also provides that a 1.0% mandatory prepayment premium applies to certain repricing transactions occurring prior to the six-month anniversary of execution of the amendment. We estimate that we incurred $2.6 million of fees and expenses in connection
	with the repricing of our first lien term loan, of which $1.9&nbsp;million is expected to be expensed in fiscal year 2016 and $0.7 million is expected to be deferred.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Dividend Increase
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	On December 16, 2016,
	we announced that our board of directors intends to increase our regular quarterly dividend from $0.14 per share to $0.16 per share, an increase of approximately 14.3%. We intend to pay a regular quarterly dividend of $0.16 per share in the first
	quarter of fiscal 2017, subject to declaration by our board of directors.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

	available, we are reporting the following estimated ranges:

	fiscal 2016 net sales of $1.566 billion to $1.569 billion, including volume growth in our three core segments (excluding volume attributable to our acquisition of Allied) of 2.8%.
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In Q4 2016, we continued to organically grow core volume, implement productivity
	initiatives as part of the APF Way, generate strong cash flow and successfully execute our acquisition strategy.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Adjusted Net Income,
	Adjusted Diluted Net Income Per Share and Adjusted EBITDA are not financial measures calculated under U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;). See &#147;&#151;Summary Historical Consolidated Financial Data&#148; for
	additional information and the tables below for a reconciliation of such non-GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable GAAP measures.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have presented preliminary estimated unaudited financial data in this prospectus because our closing procedures for Q4 2016 and fiscal 2016
	are not yet complete, and these estimates are subject to the completion of financial closing procedures, final adjustments and other developments that may arise between now and the time these results are finalized. The ranges presented herein are
	based upon the most current information available to management and assumptions we believe to be reasonable, but include information that is subject to further review, verification and adjustment. The preliminary estimated unaudited financial data
	presented herein should not be considered a substitute for the financial information to be filed with the SEC in our Annual Report on Form 10-K for fiscal 2016 once it becomes available and we have no intention or obligation to update the
	preliminary estimated unaudited financial data presented herein prior to filing our Annual Report on Form 10-K for fiscal 2016. The preliminary estimated unaudited financial data presented herein was prepared by, and is the responsibility of, our
	management. Our independent registered public accounting firm has not audited, reviewed, compiled or performed any procedures with respect to the preliminary estimated unaudited financial data, and accordingly does not express an opinion or any
	other form of assurance with respect thereto. It is possible that our final reported results for Q4 2016 and fiscal 2016 may not be within the ranges presented herein and the differences may be material, including from developments of which we are
	currently unaware. Accordingly, investors are cautioned not to place undue reliance on the preliminary estimated unaudited financial data presented herein. Please refer to &#147;Special Note Regarding Forward-Looking Statements&#148; and &#147;Risk
	Factors&#148; for additional information. The preliminary estimated unaudited financial data presented herein should be read in conjunction with &#147;Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&#148;
	and our consolidated financial statements and the related notes thereto included elsewhere in this prospectus.
</P>

<EFX_THE_OFFERING>
<A NAME="FIS_THE_OFFERING"></A>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	The Offering
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Common stock offered by the selling stockholders
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	12,500,000 shares
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Underwriters&#146; option to purchase additional shares of common stock from certain of the selling
	stockholders
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	1,875,000 shares
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Common stock to be outstanding immediately after this offering
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	78,607,804 shares
</TD>

	&nbsp;
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_6"></A>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Use of proceeds
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	We will not receive any of the proceeds from the sale of shares of common stock by the selling stockholders in this offering. However, we will bear all costs, fees and expenses in connection with this offering, except that the selling
	stockholders will pay the underwriting discounts and commissions. See &#147;Use of Proceeds.&#148;
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Risk factors
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	See &#147;Risk Factors&#148; beginning on page&nbsp;20 and other information included in this prospectus for a discussion of factors you should carefully consider before deciding to invest in our common stock.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Dividend policy
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	We paid a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.14 per share on September 28, 2016 and December 6, 2016. In addition, on December 16, 2016, we announced that our board of directors intends to increase the regular quarterly dividend from $0.14
	per share to $0.16 per share, an increase of approximately 14.3%. We expect to pay a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.16 per share beginning in the first quarter of fiscal 2017, subject to declaration by our board of directors, the discretion
	of our board of directors to increase, decrease or eliminate the dividend in the future, and compliance with applicable law, and depending on, among other things, our results of operations, financial condition, level of indebtedness, capital
	requirements, contractual restrictions, restrictions in our debt agreements and in any preferred stock, business prospects and other factors that our board of directors may deem relevant. In particular, our ability to pay dividends on our common
	stock is limited by covenants in our credit facilities and the indenture governing the notes, and may be further restricted by the terms of any future debt or preferred securities. We do not currently believe that the restrictions contained in our
	credit facilities or the indenture governing the notes will impair our ability to pay regular quarterly cash dividends as described above. Because we are a holding company, our ability to pay dividends also depends on our receipt of cash dividends
	from our operating subsidiaries, which may be restricted in their ability to pay dividends as a result of the laws of their jurisdiction of organization, agreements of our subsidiaries or covenants under any existing and future outstanding
	indebtedness we or our subsidiaries incur. See &#147;Dividend Policy&#148; and &#147;Description of Certain Indebtedness.&#148;
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD WIDTH="38%">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2%; TEXT-INDENT:-2%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	NYSE ticker symbol
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
	&#147;APFH&#148;
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	&nbsp;

<EFX_FINANCIAL_DATA>
<A NAME="FIS_FINANCIAL_DATA"></A>
<DIV STYLE ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00PT SOLID #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00PT SOLID #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0PX;MARGIN-RIGHT:0PX;WIDTH:100%">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:97%; MARGIN-TOP:1.5%; MARGIN-LEFT:1.5%; MARGIN-RIGHT:-1.25%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Summary Historical Consolidated Financial Data
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The following table summarizes our historical consolidated financial and other data for the periods and at the dates indicated. Our fiscal
	year is based on either a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	52-week
</FONT>
	or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	53-week
</FONT>
	period ending on the Saturday closest to each December&nbsp;31.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have derived the summary historical consolidated financial data for the fiscal years ended January&nbsp;2, 2016, January&nbsp;3, 2015 and
	December&nbsp;28, 2013, and the summary balance sheet data as of January&nbsp;2, 2016 and January&nbsp;3, 2015, from our audited consolidated financial statements included elsewhere in this prospectus. We have derived the summary balance sheet data
	as of December&nbsp;28, 2013 from our unaudited consolidated financial statements that are not included in this prospectus. We have derived the summary historical consolidated financial data for the 39&nbsp;weeks ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and
	October&nbsp;3, 2015, and the summary balance sheet data as of October&nbsp;1, 2016, from our unaudited consolidated interim financial statements included elsewhere in this prospectus. Our unaudited consolidated interim financial statements were
	prepared on a basis consistent with our audited consolidated financial statements and, in the opinion of management, reflect all adjustments, consisting only of normal and recurring adjustments, necessary for a fair statement of the financial
	information. We have derived the summary historical consolidated financial data for the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 by adding the summary historical consolidated financial data for the 39&nbsp;weeks ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 to the
	summary historical consolidated financial data for the fiscal year ended January&nbsp;2, 2016, and subtracting the summary historical consolidated financial data for the 39&nbsp;weeks ended October&nbsp;3, 2015. We believe that presentation of the
	summary historical consolidated financial data for the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 is useful to investors because it presents information about how our business has performed in the twelve month period immediately preceding the date of
	our most recent interim financial statements, which allows investors to review our current performance trends over a full year period, and presenting results for four consecutive quarters compensates for seasonal factors that might influence results
	in a particular quarter within the year. The results of operations of the assets of Landshire, which we acquired in January 2015, and of Better Bakery, which we acquired in April 2015, are reflected in our results as of and from the date of such
	transactions. The results of operations of Allied, which we acquired in October 2016, are not reflected in our results below.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>

</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our historical results are not necessarily indicative of future operating results, and the
	results for any interim period are not necessarily indicative of the results that may be expected for a full fiscal year. Because the data in this table is only a summary and does not provide all of the data contained in our consolidated financial
	statements, the information should be read in conjunction with &#147;Selected Historical Consolidated Financial Data,&#148; &#147;Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&#148; and our consolidated
	financial statements and the related notes thereto included elsewhere in this prospectus.

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">

	Basic net income (loss) per share is calculated based upon the weighted average number of outstanding shares of
	common stock for the period, plus the effect of vested restricted shares. Diluted net income (loss)
