<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
<A NAME="D304963DS1A_HTM_ROM304963_14">
</A>
	BUSINESS
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Company
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are a leading national
	producer and distributor of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added,
</FONT>
	convenient,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, sandwich components and other entr&eacute;es and
	snacks. We hold the number one or number two market share position by sales or volume in nearly all our major product categories, with net sales of $1.5&nbsp;billion in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and $1.6&nbsp;billion in fiscal
	2015. We offer a differentiated value proposition to our customers due to our scale, broad product portfolio, customization capabilities, national distribution and food safety track record.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We market and distribute approximately 2,600 SKUs across all day parts in multiple product categories, including:
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(1)&nbsp;ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, PB&amp;J sandwiches and hamburgers; (2)&nbsp;sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger and chicken patties and Philly steaks; and (3)&nbsp;other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as country fried steak, stuffed entr&eacute;es, chicken tenders and cinnamon dough bites. In the
	twelve months ended October 1, 2016, 67.5% of our net sales were attributable to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fast-growing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and
	sandwich components categories. Our products are shipped frozen to our customers and sold under our commercial and retail brands, as well as private label and licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We control more steps within the production process than most of our competitors. This integrated approach allows us to add value throughout
	our processes, generate attractive margins and provides us with a significant competitive advantage. Our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	processes include recipe formulation,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	pre-preparation
</FONT>
	by chopping, breading, seasoning and marinating, food preparation by baking, charring, frying and grilling, assembly and packaging. Our integrated bread and biscuit production capabilities are
	a key differentiator due to proprietary formulations that we believe produce superior tasting sandwiches.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We sell to a diverse set of
	over 3,000 customers and have an average relationship tenure of approximately 20&nbsp;years with our top 20 customers. We employ a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach, which is rooted in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	market-leading
</FONT>
	R&amp;D capabilities, product quality and customer service. We have dedicated marketing and sales teams for each of our channels to serve the specific needs of our customers. We enjoy
	&#147;category captain&#148; status in many of our product categories with our largest foodservice customers. In many cases, we collaborate with our customers to develop new products, customizing recipes and flavors in a cost efficient manner. We
	believe our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach is a competitive advantage that helps our customers grow their businesses and, in turn, accelerates our organic growth and profitability.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We sell our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	products to the foodservice, retail and convenience channels, which correspond
	to our three core segments. We also sell our products in the industrial channel. We believe our diversification across these channels provides us with a stable revenue base through economic cycles. In the twelve months ended October 1, 2016, 54.7%
	of our net sales were generated from our Foodservice segment, where our commercial brands are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers. In our Retail segment, in addition to selling
	our branded products, we also leverage our R&amp;D capabilities to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	exclusive products and packaging designs with our customers under their private label brands. In our Convenience segment, we are a
	leading supplier of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and sandwich components to national and regional convenience chains and vending providers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have an attractive financial profile with steady, organic volume growth, healthy margins, modest capital expenditures and limited working
	capital requirements. These characteristics enable our business to generate strong cash flows. Our earnings profile also benefits from a lean SG&amp;A cost structure and a scaled, efficient supply chain network. We intend to use these attributes to
	enhance stockholder value by paying regular dividends, reducing our indebtedness, strategically deploying our capital to fund organic growth opportunities and financing value-enhancing acquisitions.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	84
</P>

<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016, we generated $1.5&nbsp;billion in net sales,
	$114.8&nbsp;million in net income, $97.8&nbsp;million in Adjusted Net Income and $287.9&nbsp;million in Adjusted EBITDA. In fiscal 2015, we generated $1.6&nbsp;billion in net sales, $37.1&nbsp;million in net income, $66.8&nbsp;million in Adjusted
	Net Income and $260.2&nbsp;million in Adjusted EBITDA. Our net sales, Adjusted Net Income and Adjusted EBITDA in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 reflect a CAGR of 1.2%, 337.1% and 20.8%, respectively, since fiscal 2013. In the twelve
	months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016 and fiscal 2015, we also generated $186.6&nbsp;million and $157.2&nbsp;million, respectively, of cash flow from operating activities. See &#147;Prospectus Summary&#151;Summary Historical Consolidated Financial
	Data&#148; for reconciliations of Adjusted Net Income and Adjusted EBITDA to net income.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our History
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In September 2010, Pierre Foods,&nbsp;Inc. combined with Advance Food Company,&nbsp;Inc. and Advance Brands,&nbsp;LLC to become AdvancePierre
	Foods,&nbsp;Inc., our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	wholly-owned
</FONT>
	indirect subsidiary. Pierre Foods,&nbsp;Inc., Advance Food Company,&nbsp;Inc. and Advance Brands,&nbsp;LLC were previously privately owned and operated and held leading
	market share positions in their core product categories. Pierre Foods,&nbsp;Inc. was founded in 1946 in Cincinnati, Ohio, and held leading market positions in handheld sandwiches and other
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	meals
	and snacks, serving the foodservice, retail and convenience channels. Advance Food Company,&nbsp;Inc. was a family owned business founded in 1973 in Enid, Oklahoma, and was a leading developer, producer and marketer of a wide variety of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added,
</FONT>
	portion controlled and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-serve
</FONT>
</FONT>
	products serving the foodservice channel. Advance Brands,&nbsp;LLC was formed in
	2001 and was a leader in producing convenient chicken and beef products serving the retail channel.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In May 2011, we acquired Barber
	Foods, a leading producer and marketer of stuffed chicken breasts. The acquisition of Barber Foods expanded our retail presence and further diversified our portfolio to include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	chicken-based
</FONT>
	products.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In January 2015, we acquired the wholesale business and production operations of Landshire, an
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Illinois-based
</FONT>
	producer of premium frozen,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches. In April 2015, we acquired the business and production assets
	of Better Bakery, a producer of premium handcrafted stuffed sandwiches. In October 2016, we acquired Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products. Through these acquisitions, we further expanded our high growth and high margin
	sandwich and sandwich component portfolio while demonstrating our position as the leading platform in the industry with the ability to consolidate the fragmented industry in which we operate, integrate acquisitions successfully and generate
	meaningful sales and cost synergies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Recent Performance and the APF Way
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	During 2013 and 2014, our board of directors transformed our senior management by hiring John Simons and four of the ten other members of our
	current executive team. This new team revamped our cost structure, budgeting tools and pricing methodology by implementing a continuous improvement program that we call the &#147;APF Way.&#148; The APF Way uses a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	data-driven
</FONT>
	analytical framework to drive growth and profitability through improved commercial
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	decision-making,
</FONT>
	excellence in sales and marketing and productivity in
	procurement, logistics and production.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe the APF Way has fundamentally changed the cost structure of our business and has been a
	major factor in our recent volume, sales and profitability growth. Initially, we focused on reducing our cost structure by executing on productivity initiatives and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	re-aligning
</FONT>
	trade promotion allowances,
	resulting in approximately $155.0&nbsp;million in implemented annualized savings from 2013 to October&nbsp;1, 2016. In addition, we eliminated approximately $155.0&nbsp;million of sales associated with lower margin contracts. We have invested in new
	systems and processes that enable us to deliver continuous productivity savings and effectively manage margins and profitability. Our Adjusted EBITDA margin, which we calculate as Adjusted EBITDA divided by net sales, expanded from 10.9% in fiscal
	2013 to 18.6% in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016, even as our raw
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	85
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage92"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	material costs increased. Our net sales and volume grew at a CAGR of 2.7% and 5.2%, respectively, in our three core segments from fiscal 2013 to the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016.
	Going forward, we expect these investments and discipline will allow us to continue to deliver overall growth and attractive margins.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G00E28.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Segments
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We manage and report our operations in four segments with Foodservice, Retail and Convenience representing our core segments. Our fourth
	segment, Industrial, consists of sales to other food producers under
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	short-term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-manufacturing
</FONT>
	agreements.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G20Q53.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Foodservice.
</I>
</B>
	Our Foodservice customers include leading national and regional distributors,
	who then sell our products to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-customers
</FONT>
	such as restaurant operators, schools, healthcare providers, hospitality providers, the U.S. military and grocery deli counters. We supply 95 of the largest 100
	school districts in the United States, directly and through distributors, and work closely with school districts to develop nutritious meal options with good quality and value. We also directly supply many national restaurant chains.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We sell a diverse portfolio of products into the foodservice channel, including
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, PB&amp;J sandwiches and hamburgers, sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger and chicken patties and
	Philly steaks, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as country fried steak, stuffed entr&eacute;es, chicken tenders and cinnamon dough bites. We primarily sell our products under our own
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	commercial brands, which are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers. For fiscal 2015,
	71.5% of our Foodservice net sales were attributable to our own commercial brands, such as
<I>
	The Pub
</I>
	,
<I>
	Advance
</I>
	,
<I>
	Steak
</I>
<I>
</I>
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	-Eze
</FONT>
</I>
	,
<I>
	Philly Freedom
</I>
	and
<I>
	Smart Picks
</I>
	, and
	28.5% to private label brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	86
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage93"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	As foodservice operators attempt to differentiate and broaden their product offerings, they are
	more frequently working with
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	solution-oriented
</FONT>
	partners with strong new product development capabilities and national distribution scale, such as ourselves.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Retail.
</I>
</B>
	We serve a wide array of retail customers including national and regional grocery chains, major warehouse club stores,
	mass retailers and dollar stores.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Key products that we sell into the retail channel include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, grilled chicken sandwiches and stuffed pockets, sandwich components, such as chicken patties and Philly steaks, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such
	as stuffed chicken breasts. In addition to selling our branded products, we also leverage our R&amp;D capabilities to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	exclusive products and packaging designs with our Retail customers under their
	private label brands. For fiscal 2015, 69.4% of our Retail net sales were attributable to our retail brands, such as
<I>
	Barber
</I>
	,
<I>
	Pierre
</I>
	and
<I>
	Fast Fixin&#146;
</I>
	, 29.8% to private label brands and the rest to licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Convenience.
</I>
</B>
	The convenience channel represents an important outlet for our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and includes sales to vending providers. We currently sell to approximately 68,000 convenience locations in the United States and are the largest supplier of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches to vending providers. We currently sell to approximately 100,000 vending locations in the United States.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We partner with our Convenience customers to develop customized,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches and hamburgers, sandwich components, such as chicken patties, and other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as cinnamon
	dough bites. We are able to meet specific demands from our Convenience customers by providing private label brand products and innovative new products. For fiscal 2015, 77.6% of our Convenience net sales were attributable to our retail brands, such
	as
<I>
	Big AZ
</I>
	, 21.6% to private label brands and the rest to licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Industrial.
</I>
</B>
	In order to optimize capacity
	utilization across our production network, we opportunistically enter into
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	short-term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-manufacturing
</FONT>
	agreements with other food producers, such as packaged food
	companies. Due to the lower margin nature of this business, we have strategically reduced our percentage of net sales generated by this segment from 15.7% in fiscal 2013 to 5.1% in the twelve months ended October&nbsp;1, 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	For additional financial information about our segments, see our audited consolidated financial statements included elsewhere in this
	prospectus.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	87
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage94"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Products
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We market and distribute a broad range of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	great-tasting
</FONT>
	products across all day parts in multiple
	product categories, including:
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(1)&nbsp;ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches, such as breakfast sandwiches, PB&amp;J sandwiches and hamburgers; (2)&nbsp;sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger and chicken patties and Philly steaks; and (3)&nbsp;other entr&eacute;es and snacks, such as country fried steak, stuffed entr&eacute;es, chicken tenders, popcorn chicken and cinnamon dough
	bites. We market and distribute approximately 2,600 SKUs across all day parts to a diverse mix of customers in our Foodservice, Retail, Convenience and Industrial segments. Many of our products have been customized to fit specific customer needs. In
	the twelve months ended October 1, 2016, 67.5% of our net sales were attributable to the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fast-growing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and
	sandwich components categories. Our products are shipped frozen to our customers and sold under our commercial and retail brands, as well as private label and licensed brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G72I21.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Ready
</I>
</B>
<B>
<I>
</I>
</B>
<B>
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	-to
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
<B>
<I>
</I>
</B>
<B>
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	-Eat
</FONT>
	Sandwiches.
</I>
</B>
	We are the largest manufacturer of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	lunch and dinner sandwiches. We produce over 600&nbsp;million sandwiches per year, which are
	shipped frozen to our customers. We possess vertically integrated bakery, production and assembly capabilities which differentiate us from our competitors and support high margins in this product category. Our superior bread quality is an important
	purchase driver for our sandwiches. Our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches are sold under a variety of our own brands, such as
<I>
	Big AZ
</I>
	,
<I>
	Pierre
</I>
	,
<I>
	Landshire
</I>
	and
<I>
	Better Bakery
</I>
	, licensed brands and several leading private label brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Sandwich Components.
</I>
</B>
	We are a leading
	producer of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	great-tasting
</FONT>
	sandwich components, such as
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	hamburger patties (sold under
<I>
	The Pub
</I>
	brand), Philly steaks (sold under the
<I>
	Steak
</I>
<I>
</I>
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	-EZE
</FONT>
</I>
	brand), pork rib patties, chicken patties, meatballs and fajita steaks. All of our sandwich components are also offered under leading private label distributor brands in our
	Foodservice segment and leading private label brands.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Other Entr&eacute;es and Snacks.
</I>
</B>
	We are a leading producer of
	convenient entr&eacute;es and snacks, including stuffed entr&eacute;es (sold under the
<I>
	Barber Foods
</I>
	brand), country fried steak (sold under the
<I>
	Advance
</I>
	brand), chicken tenders (sold under the
<I>
	Fast Fixin&#146;
</I>
	brand), popcorn
	chicken and cinnamon dough bites.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Strengths
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe the following strengths differentiate us from our competitors and will contribute to our ongoing success:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Leading Market Positions in Attractive, Growing Categories
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We hold the number one or number two market share position by volume in nearly all of our major product categories and are well positioned to
	capitalize on growth in our markets. We are the number one player with market shares ranging from approximately 30% to 65% in our top five product categories, which represent 68% of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Within most of our major product
	categories, we are the only
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	full-service
</FONT>
	operator of scale and compete against smaller, regional players with limited product breadth, production capacity and capabilities. We typically do not compete against
	large packaged food companies given our foodservice focus and the customization requirements of our customers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	89
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage96"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We produce over 600&nbsp;million sandwiches per year and 67.5% of our net sales in the twelve
	months ended October 1, 2016 were related to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwiches and sandwich components. We are a leading provider of lunch and dinner sandwiches to the
	foodservice, retail and convenience channels. Our superior bread quality is an important purchase driver for our sandwiches.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/01/17/0001193125-17-010403_G304963G39I04.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Long-Standing,
</FONT>
	Collaborative Customer Relationships Create a
	High Barrier to Entry
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our strong customer relationships across a diverse set of customers provide a significant competitive
	advantage and create a high barrier to entry. For fiscal 2015, our top ten customers accounted for 53.4% of our net sales, with our two largest customers, Sysco Corporation and U.S.&nbsp;Foods,&nbsp;Inc., accounting for 13.6% and 12.0%,
	respectively, of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Our two largest customers collectively source over 1,700 SKUs from our portfolio and buy across multiple contracts for a diverse set of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-customers,
</FONT>
	making us
	an important supplier and giving us a stable and consistent revenue base.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have deep and collaborative relationships with an average
	tenure of approximately 20&nbsp;years with our top 20 customers. We maintain our relationships through our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	segment-focused
</FONT>
	marketing teams and an experienced sales force of approximately 100 associates who
	work closely with customers to meet their needs. Our foodservice commercial brands are highly
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sought-after
</FONT>
	and trusted by chefs, cooks and other purchasers for their consistent food safety, premium quality and
	taste profile. Given our track record, we enjoy &#147;category captain&#148; status in many of our product categories. We produce approximately 2,600 SKUs for our customers, who source a high volume and a variety of products from us, making us an
	important supplier and partner. We expect to continue to have a competitive advantage as our customers focus on large scale suppliers in order to streamline and optimize their supply chains.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We offer a differentiated value proposition to our customers due to our scale, broad product portfolio, customization capabilities, national
	distribution and food safety track record.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	90
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage97"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Leader in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	On-Trend,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Fast-to-Market
</FONT>
</FONT>
	New Product Development
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe
	our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	approach, which is rooted in
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	market-leading
</FONT>
	R&amp;D capabilities, product quality and customer service, differentiates us from our competitors and
	has allowed us to accelerate our organic growth and improve our profitability. Our product innovation and R&amp;D expertise span areas such as flavor development, recipe formulation, nutrition science, bakery science and food safety. In recent
	years, we have enhanced our new product development and customer insight capabilities, and, in 2015, we opened a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	state-of-the-art
</FONT>
</FONT>
</FONT>
	3,200 square foot R&amp;D facility in West Chester, Ohio.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The food industry today is characterized by rapidly changing menus and evolving
	consumer taste profiles. In this environment, our customers value our ability to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	new products with flavor profiles that differentiate their offerings and successfully commercialize new products with
	speed and efficiency. We launched 600 new SKUs in the last three years, accounting for 12.7% of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Our innovation, sales force and marketing teams collaborate with customers to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	highly customized products and are able to mobilize quickly to respond to customer requests.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Scale and Production Efficiency with a National Distribution Footprint
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We benefit from a national, scaled production, procurement and logistics network with low production, freight and warehousing costs. We believe
	our efficient cost structure provides a sustainable competitive advantage and enables us to offer a customized and varied set of products to our customers at competitive prices.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have two integrated bakery facilities which allow us to source approximately 65% of our bread
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-house
</FONT>
	(excluding bread for our PB&amp;J sandwiches). Our eleven production facilities benefit from economies of scale, which when combined with our national distribution capabilities, differentiate us from
	our competitors and make us a valuable supplier for both national and regional customers. Except for the production facility previously owned by Allied, which we acquired in October 2016 and are in the process of improving, all of our facilities
	have achieved SQF Level&nbsp;3 food safety certification, the highest level of such certification from GFSI.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Attractive Financial
	Profile
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have an attractive financial profile with steady, organic volume growth in our core segments, healthy Adjusted EBITDA
	margins, modest capital expenditures and limited working capital requirements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are able to deliver attractive Adjusted EBITDA margins
	due to the high
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	nature of our products. Our margin profile is well protected given our ability to proactively adjust pricing frequently to reflect input cost movements with minimal lag time. Only
	16.2% of our net sales in fiscal 2015 were subject to fixed price arrangements. We also have a lean and scalable cost structure. We plan to continue leveraging the APF Way to deliver operational productivity savings, improve our business mix and
	increase the effectiveness of our trade promotion allowances. Our business has relatively low capital expenditure requirements, with maintenance expenditures typically averaging approximately 1% of our net sales.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Proven Acquisition Expertise
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have a successful track record of sourcing, executing and integrating acquisitions, beginning with the combination of Pierre
	Foods,&nbsp;Inc., APF&#146;s predecessor, with Advance Food Company,&nbsp;Inc. and Advance Brands,&nbsp;LLC in 2010. Given our scale and breadth of capabilities, we believe we are well positioned to consolidate the fragmented industry in which we
	operate. We maintain a highly disciplined approach to acquisitions, focusing on opportunities that diversify our products, add production capabilities, expand production capacity and allow for meaningful synergy realization. In addition to realizing
	cost synergies, we leverage our sales teams to expand distribution of newly acquired brands and products and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	cross-sell
</FONT>
	across our channels to drive sales synergies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	91
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage98"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Since 2011, we have completed four accretive acquisitions. In June 2011, we acquired Barber
	Foods, a producer of premium stuffed entr&eacute;es, which strengthened our retail presence and expanded our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	chicken-based
</FONT>
	product offering. In January 2015, we acquired the wholesale business and production
	assets of Landshire, which broadened our portfolio of premium sandwiches to include sliced meat sandwiches and added incremental,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	margin-enhancing
</FONT>
	baking and assembly production capabilities. In April 2015, we
	acquired the business and production assets of Better Bakery to expand into stuffed sandwiches, one of the largest
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	sandwich categories. Our acquisitions of
	Barber Foods, Landshire and Better Bakery contributed $166.4&nbsp;million of incremental net sales in fiscal 2015. In October 2016, we acquired Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products, which we expect will expand our leading
	position in Philly steaks by adding fully cooked product offerings, expand our geographic reach and increase our sandwich component production capacity.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Talented Management Team with a Track Record of Driving Growth and Reducing Costs
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Since 2013, we have assembled an experienced management team through strategic hiring of key leaders and expanded organizational capabilities
	in R&amp;D, sales and marketing. Our management team has an average of 25&nbsp;years of expertise in the foodservice, retail and convenience industries and has demonstrated its ability to deliver on key strategic initiatives, which have transformed
	business performance. In the last two years, our management team&#146;s key accomplishments include implementation of the APF Way, successful integration of two
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-enhancing
</FONT>
	acquisitions and significant
	margin improvement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our management team had been led by our President and Chief Executive Officer John Simons since October 2013. On
	November&nbsp;9, 2016, in response to Mr.&nbsp;Simons&#146; planned retirement in 2017, we announced a succession and transition plan for our President and Chief Executive Officer positions. As a part of the plan, Christopher Sliva, who has over a
	decade of experience as a public food company executive, became our President and a member of our board of directors. It is anticipated that Mr.&nbsp;Simons will remain as our Chief Executive Officer until March&nbsp;31, 2017, when he will retire
	and be succeeded by Mr.&nbsp;Sliva as our President and Chief Executive Officer.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Strategy
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Expand Our Market Leading Positions in Growing Channels and Categories
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are focused on expanding our leadership position within our core segments of Foodservice, Retail and Convenience.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	breakfast sandwich category is a
	key growth opportunity for us. We hold the number one position with a 64% market share in breakfast sandwiches sold in the convenience channel. We are also the largest supplier of private label breakfast sandwiches in the retail channel, with a 56%
	market share, according to IRI data prepared in 2016. Private label sales of retail frozen breakfast sandwiches are underpenetrated compared to the frozen food market and therefore we believe poised for significant growth. We will continue to
	leverage our sandwich expertise and customer relationships to grow our share in breakfast sandwiches in the retail channel and with foodservice distributors and schools.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe we have multiple growth opportunities across our core segments. In Foodservice, we plan to expand distribution of our products to
	new customers, such as coffee shops, theaters, grocery deli counters and hospitality providers. In Retail, in addition to growing our sandwich business, we are launching product extensions for
<I>
	Barber Foods
</I>
	and
<I>
	Better Bakery
</I>
	and
	expanding distribution within rapidly growing dollar stores. In Convenience, we are expanding our breakfast product portfolio and launching
<I>
	Better Bakery
</I>
	products.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are also expanding our lineup of products to take advantage of recent consumer trends. We have successfully launched
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	snacking-oriented
</FONT>
	products, such as popcorn chicken, PB&amp;J snack bars and cinnamon dough bites, and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	better-for-you
</FONT>
</FONT>
	products, such as
	antibiotic,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	hormone-free
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	fully-cooked
</FONT>
	burgers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	92
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage99"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Drive Growth Through Focus on Innovation
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our product categories offer potential for
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	product innovation. We believe our innovation
	capabilities, combined with our investments in consumer insights and our ability to partner with customers to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-create
</FONT>
	products, will enable us to continue to introduce successful new products to drive sales
	growth and margin improvement across our portfolio.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our R&amp;D team is focused on developing products in line with key consumer trends,
	such as breakfast sandwiches,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	better-for-you
</FONT>
</FONT>
	products and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	snacking-oriented
</FONT>
	products. Examples of products in our innovation
	pipeline include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	breakfast sandwiches that meet the new
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	K-12
</FONT>
	nutrition guidelines, premium offerings for club stores
	and new limited time offers for key convenience store chain customers. We are also partnering with various customers to develop
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	on-trend,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	protein-based
</FONT>
	snacks.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Deliver Attractive Margins through Dynamic Pricing and Leveraging the APF Way
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe we are well positioned to deliver attractive margins given the high
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-added
</FONT>
	nature of
	our products, our dynamic pricing model and our ability to generate ongoing productivity savings by leveraging the APF Way. In addition, our focus on improving our product mix, leveraging our scalable organization structure and realizing synergies
	from acquisitions supports our margin profile. Under the APF Way, we are implementing multiple initiatives across the areas of production, procurement, commercial and logistics that we expect will deliver ongoing productivity savings and help offset
	potential operational headwinds and cost inflation.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Acquire
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Value-Enhancing
</FONT>
	Businesses
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe our scale and integration expertise allow us to make
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	value-enhancing
</FONT>
	acquisitions. We operate in a highly fragmented industry with many opportunities to execute accretive transactions. For example, in October 2016, we acquired Allied, a producer of beef and chicken Philly steak products, which we expect will expand
	our market position in Philly steaks by adding fully cooked product offerings, expand our geographic reach and increase our sandwich component production capacity. Our integration expertise allows us to rapidly capture cost synergies and we are able
	to generate revenue synergies by leveraging existing customer relationships and marketing expertise to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	cross-sell
</FONT>
	products across channels. Our management team has an active pipeline of acquisition
	opportunities and maintains a regular dialogue with potential targets.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Return Capital and Reduce Debt
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe our capital structure enables us to invest in our business and reduce our indebtedness, creating value for our stockholders. We also
	expect to return capital to our stockholders through regular dividend payments. We paid a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.14 per share on September 28, 2016 and December 6, 2016. In addition, on December 16, 2016, we announced that our board
	of directors intends to increase the regular quarterly dividend from $0.14 per share to $0.16 per share, an increase of approximately 14.3%. We expect to pay a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.16 per share beginning in the first quarter of
	fiscal 2017, subject to declaration by our board of directors. See &#147;Dividend Policy&#148; for additional details.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Customers
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We have a few large customers that account for a significant portion of our sales. Sysco Corporation and U.S. Foods,&nbsp;Inc. accounted for
	13.6% and 12.0%, respectively, of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Our two largest customers source over 1,700 SKUs from our portfolio and buy across multiple contracts for a diverse set of
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-customers,
</FONT>
	making
	us an important supplier and giving us a stable and consistent sales base.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	No other customer accounted for more than 10% of our net sales
	in fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 or fiscal 2013. Cumulatively, our top ten customers accounted for 53.4%, 54.7% and 54.6% of our net sales in fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	93
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage100"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Customers located in the United States account for almost all of our net sales. Sales to
	customers located outside of the United States totaled $15.4&nbsp;million, $20.0&nbsp;million and $22.7&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013, respectively. None of our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	long-lived
</FONT>
	assets
	were located outside of the United States during fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 or fiscal 2013.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Sales and Distribution Functions
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We maintain sales and distribution functions to support sales within our three core segments. We have approximately 140 employees within our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	segment-specific
</FONT>
	sales and marketing teams and also rely on our 17 member customer service team. In addition, our 42 member demand management team manages customer forecasts, orders, deliveries and feedback.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Foodservice.
</I>
</B>
	We employ approximately 30 marketing professionals, 75 direct sales representatives and 14 national and regional
	brokers to service our diverse set of foodservice customers. We have a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Foodservice-specific
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	go-to-market
</FONT>
</FONT>
	team that enables us to
	develop tailored marketing and sales solutions for our customers. Our marketing and sales teams directly interact with major participants in the foodservice distribution chain, including distributors, redistributors, contract management companies,
	group purchasing organizations and large
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-use
</FONT>
	operators. We service the majority of our foodservice customers through distributors but also ship directly to select foodservice customers including large
	school districts, select national restaurant chains and the U.S. military.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Retail.
</I>
</B>
	We employ approximately 15 marketing
	professionals, 15 direct sales representatives and 41 national and regional brokers to service our retail customers. Our sales and marketing teams are designed to provide direct support to our top retail customers to facilitate responsive and rapid
	product development, in addition to effective
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-store
</FONT>
	promotion planning and execution. For smaller customers, we work closely with our network of broker sales teams to meet customer needs. Most retail
	customers either pick up products at our distribution centers or request that we deliver products to their distribution centers. Some smaller customers, however, receive shipments through redistributors that pick up products from our distribution
	centers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Convenience.
</I>
</B>
	We employ six marketing professionals, nine direct sales representatives and nine national and
	regional brokers to service our convenience customers. We have designed our sales and marketing teams to provide direct support to our top convenience customers to facilitate responsive and rapid product development, in addition to effective
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-store
</FONT>
	promotion planning and execution. For smaller customers, we work closely with our network of broker sales teams and distributors that deliver products to stores. The majority of large convenience customers
	receive products through distributors, while smaller convenience customers often receive products through national and regional distributors.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In addition to the above, we have two sales representatives who work within our Industrial segment and are responsible for sourcing business
	to fill any excess capacity identified within our production facilities.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our distribution centers are located in Enid, Oklahoma,
	Cincinnati, Ohio and Rockmart, Georgia. Approximately
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	one-third
</FONT>
	of our volume is picked up at our production facilities or distribution centers by our customers. For the remainder of our volume, we utilize
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	third-party
</FONT>
	logistics providers to deliver products to customer and redistributor warehouses.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our R&amp;D
	Capabilities
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In recent years, we have enhanced our new product development and customer insight capabilities, and in 2015, we opened a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	state-of-the-art
</FONT>
</FONT>
</FONT>
	3,200 square foot R&amp;D facility in West Chester, Ohio. Our R&amp;D expertise spans the spectrum of food
	development, from meat technology and flavor development to production and processing ingredients, bakery science and nutrition formulation.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	94
</P>

<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In addition, our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	customer-centric
</FONT>
	model allows us to
	quickly respond to customer requests, particularly as we
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	co-develop
</FONT>
	products with our customers to bring new ideas to the market. We station satellite R&amp;D teams in our production facilities where they can
	directly leverage the facilities&#146; capabilities when developing and scaling new products. Our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-house
</FONT>
	R&amp;D team is based in West Chester, Ohio and consists of over 50 professionals including chefs,
	food scientists and food development experts who are focused on new product development,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	product-quality
</FONT>
	improvements, productivity improvements and package development.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We introduced 179, 172 and 192 new SKUs in fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013, respectively. New products released during fiscal 2015,
	fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013 accounted for 12.7% of our net sales in fiscal 2015. Our R&amp;D expenditures totaled $6.6&nbsp;million, $6.0&nbsp;million and $4.7&nbsp;million for fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014 and fiscal 2013, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our R&amp;D team is currently focused on developing
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	on-trend
</FONT>
	products, such as handheld breakfast
	sandwiches and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	better-for-you
</FONT>
</FONT>
	and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	snacking-oriented
</FONT>
	products. Examples of projects in our innovation pipeline include
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	ready-to-eat
</FONT>
</FONT>
	breakfast sandwiches that meet the new
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	K-12
</FONT>
	nutrition guidelines, premium offerings for club stores and new limited time
	offers for key convenience store chain customers. We are also partnering with various customers to develop
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	on-trend,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	protein-based
</FONT>
	snacks.
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Properties
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Our production and
	distribution network consists of eleven production facilities and three strategically located distribution centers in the United States. Our production facilities include two integrated bakery facilities which allow us to source approximately 65% of
	our bread
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	in-house
</FONT>
	(excluding bread for our PB&amp;J sandwiches).

	following eleven production facilities, which are used to produce products sold in all four of our segments:

	The lenders under our credit facilities have a lien on all of our owned properties. See &#147;Description of
	Certain Indebtedness.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We lease our distribution center in Enid, Oklahoma and have contracted for warehouse space in our
	distribution centers in Cincinnati, Ohio and Rockmart, Georgia. In 2012, we sold our distribution center in Enid, Oklahoma and entered into a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	long-term
</FONT>
	lease with the buyer through a sale leaseback
	transaction. We also lease our corporate headquarters in Blue Ash, Ohio.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are in the process of building a new 70,000 square foot
	production facility in Vineland, New Jersey, which we expect to complete in the first quarter of fiscal 2017.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Our Ingredients and Packaging
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe that the ingredients and packaging used to produce our products are readily available through multiple sources. Our ingredients
	primarily include beef, poultry, pork, bread and breadings, cheese, eggs, seasonings, soy proteins, corn and packaging supplies. Packaging materials account for a significantly smaller portion of our costs of goods sold than our ingredients. We
	enter into various purchasing arrangements with certain suppliers, including suppliers of protein, seasoning and packing supplies, in order to mitigate the impact of commodity cost fluctuations. We have not historically entered into any hedging
	agreements for our ingredients or packaging supplies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Quality and Food Safety
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We believe that quality and food safety are paramount. As a result, we have developed, implemented and enforced a robust quality and food
	safety program.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	All of our production facilities&#146; quality control teams are independent and report directly to our corporate quality
	and food safety team, a central function comprised of approximately 17 employees under the Senior Vice President, Quality, who reports directly to our President. This creates strong accountability at the senior level for the quality and safety of
	our products. We have approximately 175 salaried and hourly quality control employees who are located at our production facilities.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We
	have implemented the SQF program at all of our facilities. SQF is a fully integrated food safety and quality management protocol designed by GFSI specifically for the food sector. The SQF code offers a comprehensive methodology to manage food safety
	and quality simultaneously. SQF certification by GFSI provides an independent and external validation that a product, process or service complies with international, regulatory and other specified standards. Except for the production facility
	previously owned by Allied, which we acquired in October 2016, all of our production facilities have achieved SQF Level&nbsp;3 food safety certification, the highest level of such certification from GFSI. We also maintain systems in all of our
	factories that verify and validate compliance with federal, state and local regulations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We source the raw materials used in our products
	from a variety of high quality
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	USDA-regulated
</FONT>
	suppliers and we believe high quality raw material are available from multiple sources. In order to protect the quality and safety of our products, we regularly
	inspect our suppliers&#146; production facilities and delivered products.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	As part of our quality and food safety program, our
	professionals continuously work with the applicable regulatory agencies, including the USDA and the FDA, the academic community, trade associations and our industry partners to stay informed of emerging issues and improve our quality and food safety
	program.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Despite our commitment to quality and food safety, we have previously issued recalls for our products. See &#147;Risk
	Factors&#151;Risks Related to Our Business&#151;If our products become contaminated or are mislabeled, we may be subject to product liability claims, product recalls and increased scrutiny by regulators, any of which could adversely affect our
	business.&#148;
</P>
</EFX_PROPERTIES>
<EFX_COMPETITION>
<A NAME="FIS_COMPETITION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Competition
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We face
	competition in each of our respective product categories and end markets. Although we operate in a highly competitive industry, we believe that the breadth and depth of our product portfolio and product quality have resulted in strong market share
	positions. Within most of our major product categories, we are the only
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	full-service
</FONT>
	operator of scale and compete against smaller, regional players with limited product breadth, production capacity and
	production capabilities. We typically do not compete against large packaged food companies given our foodservice focus and the customization requirements of our customers. Smaller players include American Food Group, CTI Foods, Devault Foods, Lopez
	Foods and JTM Food Group. In certain product categories such as breakfast sandwiches and entr&eacute;es and snacks, we compete with larger players such as Hormel, Hillshire, Nestle and Smuckers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	96
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage103"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We compete on the basis of, among other things, product quality, total product portfolio, price,
	customer service, ability to meet customer demands, effective consumer marketing, promotional activities and the ability to identify and satisfy emerging consumer preferences.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Information Systems
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We operate a single
	enterprise resource planning (&#147;ERP&#148;) system for substantially all of our facilities for operations, procurement, receiving, warehousing, inventory management and order processing. We also have an integrated suite of supporting financial,
	demand planning and material requirements planning (&#147;MRP&#148;) software modules that are effectively integrated into our core ERP platform. This
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	enterprise-wide
</FONT>
	systems platform provides us with four key
	advantages. First, it provides us with
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	real-time
</FONT>
	financial and operational reports that enable rapid
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	decision-making
</FONT>
	and execution. Second, we efficiently process orders
	and ship to our customers on a &#147;one order, one invoice&#148; basis. Third, we can efficiently and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	cost-effectively
</FONT>
	manage the forecasting, production and inventory complexity associated with our portfolio
	of approximately 2,600 SKUs. Finally, our common information technology allows us to integrate acquisitions and achieve synergies quickly.
</P>
</EFX_COMPETITION>
<EFX_EMPLOYEES>
<A NAME="FIS_EMPLOYEES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Employees
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	As of October&nbsp;1, 2016, we had approximately 4,200 employees with approximately 900 salaried employees, and none of our employees
	were unionized. Allied, which we acquired in October 2016, has approximately 90 unionized employees. The collective bargaining agreement covering these employees expires in April&nbsp;2020. Although we have not experienced any significant labor
	disputes or work stoppages, and we believe that we have good relationships with our employees, including those who are union members, increased unionization or a work stoppage because of our failure to renegotiate union contracts could have a
	material adverse effect on us. See &#147;Risk Factors&#151;Risks Related to Our Business&#151;Labor disruptions or increased labor costs could adversely affect our business, financial condition and operating results.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Government, Legal and Regulatory
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Food Safety, Product Identity, Branding and Labeling
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are subject to extensive regulation, including, among others, the Federal Meat Inspection Act of 1906, the Food, Drug and Cosmetic Act of
	1938, the Poultry Products Inspection Act of 1957, the Nutrition Labeling and Education Act of 1990, the USDA HACCP
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Mega-Reg
</FONT>
	of 1996, the Public Health Security and Bioterrorism Preparedness&nbsp;&amp;
	Response Act of 2002, the Food Safety Modernization Act of 2011 and other rules and regulations promulgated by the FDA, the United States Department of Agriculture and the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	sub-branches
</FONT>
	of these regulatory
	bodies pertaining to the production and introduction of human foods to commerce. These comprehensive and evolving regulatory programs govern, among other things, the manufacturing, composition, ingredients, labeling, packaging and safety of food,
	including compliance with specific current good manufacturing practice regulations. In addition, the Nutrition Labeling and Education Act of 1990 prescribes the format and content of certain specific information required to appear on the labels of
	food products.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In addition to complying with federal laws and regulations pertaining to food production, we are also required to comply
	with local municipality (city and county) as well as state regulations, including the registration and licensing of our plants, enforcement by state health agencies of various state standards and inspection of our facilities.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Compliance with federal, state and local regulation is costly and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	time-consuming,
</FONT>
	but one of our top
	priorities. Regulatory enforcement actions for violations of federal, state and local regulations may include seizure and condemnation of products, mandatory or voluntary product recalls, cease and desist orders, injunctions and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	monetary-civil-criminal
</FONT>
</FONT>
	penalties. We believe that our practices are sufficient to maintain compliance with applicable government regulations, although there can be no
	assurances in this regard. It is also
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	97
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage104"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D304963DS1A_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	possible that new laws or regulations, or changes in the enforcement of existing requirements, might require us to change our compliance programs, incur additional costs or result in unexpected
	liabilities that could be significant.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Employee Safety Regulations
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are subject to certain health and safety regulations, including regulations issued pursuant to the Occupational Safety and Health Act. These
	regulations require us to comply with certain manufacturing, health and safety standards to protect our employees from accidents.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<I>
	Environmental Regulations
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We are subject to federal, state and local environmental regulations and requirements, including those governing discharges to air and water,
	the management of hazardous substances, the disposal of solid and hazardous wastes and the remediation of contamination. Failure to comply with these regulations can have serious consequences for us, including criminal as well as civil and
	administrative penalties, limitations on our operations, claims for remediation costs, as well as alleged personal injury or property damages and negative publicity. We are involved from time to time in administrative or legal proceedings relating
	to environmental and health and safety matters, and have incurred and will continue to incur capital and operating expenditures to avoid violations of these laws and regulations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Based on current information, we do not believe that any costs we may incur relating to environmental matters will have a material adverse
	effect on our business, financial position or results of operations. However, there can be no guarantee that newly discovered information, more stringent enforcement of or changes in environmental requirements, or other unanticipated events will not
	result in significant costs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Insurance
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	We maintain general liability and product liability, product contamination, property, worker&#146;s compensation, business interruption,
	director and officer and other insurance in amounts and on terms that we believe are customary for companies similarly situated. In addition, we maintain excess insurance where we reasonably believe it is cost effective.
</P>
</EFX_EMPLOYEES>
<EFX_LEGAL_PROCEEDINGS>
<A NAME="FIS_LEGAL_PROCEEDINGS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Legal Proceedings
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:4%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	From time to time, we
	may be party to litigation that arises in the ordinary course of our business. While it is not feasible to predict or determine the ultimate outcome of these matters, we believe that any ultimate liability with respect to any pending litigation will
	not adversely affect our business, financial condition and operating results.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:1.00EM; TEXT-INDENT:-1.00EM; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
